    • Method Detail

      • getIdentifier

        protected java.lang.String getIdentifier()
        Returns the 4-byte identifier this atom uses. These identifiers are often defined in the QT file format.

        (Although this uses a java.lang.String, serious badness will follow if this value is not exactly 4-bytes long.

        Returns:
        the 4-byte identifier this atom uses (such as "moov", "trak", etc.)

      • getSize

        protected long getSize()
        Returns the complete size of this atom, including the 8 byte header that is not written in the writeContents method.

        Subclasses are encouraged to override this method if it is easy to calculate the number of bytes that will be written. By default this method uses a NullOutputStream to actually write the data and measure its length.

        Returns:
        the complete size of this atom.

      • writeContents

        protected void writeContents(GuardedOutputStream out)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Writes the contents of this atom, minus the first 8 bytes. This is called from the write() method.

        (The first 8 bytes are always the size of this atom, and its identifier. Those are already written when this is called.)

        Parameters:
        out - a GuardedOutputStream that is restricted to write only a fixed number of bytes.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
